					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the village.</p>						

						<p>Achyutarāya. 1536-37 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of date, <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi>, Duṉmukhi, daśami, Tiruvōṇam are insufficient for verfication. The cyclic year will however correspond to 1536-37 A.D. falling within the reign of Achyuta.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the assignment of the income from <hi rend="italic">jōḍi</hi> realised from Tiruvandavāṟu for worship to the local deity (name lost) by Tīttāra Piḷḷai for the merit of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
